Plurk Notify: A Plurk Notification Monitor for GNOME
Feature:
1. notify new plurks
2. display unread plurks count, when hover on the icon and right click.
3. left click to open plurk.com in your default to

To install, copy the folder to wherever you like. 
Execute plurknotify.py to start the program.
Put it to startup application if you prefer.
Create a file called 'password.dat' in the folder where plurknotify.py is locate, with username in the first line, password in the second line.

